---
// About Section
---

<section id="about" class="py-20 bg-zinc-950">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
    <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-16 text-center">
      About Me
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
      <div class="flex justify-center">
        <img
          src="/084C3151-D277-45C4-8174-1C757AEBBE51.JPG"
          alt="Jennifer Miranda"
          width="320"
          height="384"
          class="w-80 h-96 object-cover rounded-2xl shadow-2xl shadow-violet-500/20 border-2 border-violet-500/30"
          style="object-position: center 30%;"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          Recent Computer Science graduate from California State University, Bakersfield (May 2025), currently interning at FWD Dynamics where I lead code reviews, facilitate scrum ceremonies, and collaborate on product strategy.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          I build full-stack applications with a backend focus. My experience spans from building real-time automation tools deployed on Digital Ocean to developing scalable RESTful APIs and tutoring students in data structures, algorithms, object-oriented programming, and best practices in code quality.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          When I'm not coding, you'll find me reading, trying new recipes, or catching up on movies. I'm open to opportunities where I can contribute, learn, and build software that matters.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
